---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import GeometryCanvas from '../../../components/diagrams/GeometryCanvas.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Areas and Solids" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-8/" backLabel="← Grade 8">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Areas and Solids</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Surface area and volume of prisms and cylinders</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>From 2D to 3D</h2>
		<p>A prism is created by "pulling" a flat shape upward. Volume = base area × height. Surface area = 2 × base + lateral surface.</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Base Areas</h3>
		<p>Change the triangular base — the prism volume is this area times the height!</p>
	</section>

	<GeometryCanvas client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Formulas</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Prism:</strong> V = B · h, SA = 2B + lateral</li>
			<li><strong>Cylinder:</strong> V = π·r²·h, SA = 2·π·r² + 2·π·r·h</li>
			<li><strong>Pyramid:</strong> V = ⅓ · B · h</li>
			<li><strong>Cone:</strong> V = ⅓ · π·r² · h</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Remember: Pointed solids (pyramid, cone) have ⅓ the volume of their "straight" relatives!</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
